    Even the simplest environmental stimuli elicit responses in large
  populations of neurons in early sensory cortical areas. How these distributed
  responses are read out by subsequent processing stages to mediate behavior
  remains unknown. Here we used voltage-sensitive dye imaging to measure
  directly population responses in the primary visual cortex (V1) of monkeys
