  directionally selective middle temporal (MT) neurons, leading to
  characteristic tuning curves. We show that such tuning emerges in a
  stochastic recurrent network, for a set of connectivity parameters that
  overlaps with a single-state scenario and multistability. Information
  theoretic analysis shows that second-order statistics carry information that
  can improve the accuracy of the population code.%
