    \field{abstract}{%
    Neurons in the primate Middle Temporal (MT) area signal information about
  visual motion and work together with the lateral prefrontal cortex (LPFC) to
  support memory-guided comparisons of visual motion direction. These areas are
  reciprocally connected, and both contain neurons that signal visual motion
